President Obama announced his intent to nominate Aaron Williams as the Director of the Peace Corps. Williams has over 25 years of experience in worldwide assistance programs and has held senior positions at the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) and the International Youth Foundation. He has led a billion-dollar foreign assistance program in South Africa and has extensive experience in Latin America, Africa, Asia, and the Middle East. Williams is a former Peace Corps Volunteer and is fluent in Spanish. He is a member of the Council on Foreign Relations and serves on the advisory board of the Ron Brown Scholar Program, the board of directors of CARE, and the National Peace Corps Association.